        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(runtime): prevent resource leaks and silent failures [AI-assisted]",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFix 3 resource leaks / crash paths and 1 silent failure mode discovered during a stability audit.\n\n## Changes\n\n| File | Problem | Fix |\n|------|---------|-----|\n| `media/server.ts` | `setInterval` handle never saved; leaks on every config reload | Save handle, `clearInterval` on `server.close` and error path |\n| `agents/subagent-announce-capture.ts` | `readSubagentOutput` in retry loop has no try/catch; read error kills agent | Wrap in try/catch, treat error as empty / continue retrying |\n| `hooks/gmail-watcher.ts` | `gog` crash → fixed 5s restart loop forever; CPU/log explosion | Exponential backoff 5s → 60s cap; reset on successful spawn |\n| `config/io.ts` | Config parse/read errors silently return `{}` with zero logs | Add `warn` logs before fallback to empty config |\n\n## Cleanup\n\n- Deleted `src/i18n/registry.test.ts` — this directory only contained a test file that tested `ui/src/i18n/lib/registry.ts`. No production code was affected.\n\n## Risk\n\n- All changes are additive or affect error paths only. Happy-path behavior is unchanged.\n- The gmail-watcher backoff only triggers when `gog` is already crashing; success path is identical.\n\n## Testing\n\n- [x] `pnpm build` passes\n- [x] `pnpm check:changed` passes\n- [x] `src/media/server.test.ts` — 12/13 pass (1 unrelated Windows symlink EPERM)\n- [x] `src/config/io.best-effort.test.ts` — 2/2 pass",
